title: Pastor Ryan’s Cajun Meatloaf
summary: The recipe Pastor Ryan’s Cajun Meatloaf could satisfy your Creole craving in around 1 hour and 20 minutes. For $2.65 per serving, you get a main course that serves 8. One serving contains 584 calories, 40g of protein, and 29g of fat. 339 people were glad they tried this recipe. If you have salt, honey, butter, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the whole eggs you could follow this main course with the Rose Levy Beranbaum's Chocolate Tomato Cake with Mystery Ganache as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 87%. This score is amazing. Similar recipes are Pastor Ryan’s Bolognese Sauce, Pastor Ryan’s Mexican Lasagna, and Pastor Ryan’s Pasta Carbonara.

winePairing.pairingText: Cajun on the menu? Try pairing with Albarino, Sauvignon Blanc, and rosé Wine. These low-tannin, lower alcohol wines will complement the heat in spicy cajun dishes, instead of making your mouth burn more. You could try Viontan Albarino. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.1 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 15 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Vionta Albarino
productMatches.description: Mild lemon gold, with a pale trim. Clean, fresh,lychee and herb butter nose. Warm and elegant.Fabulous fine, ripe pear palate with some oreganoand melon behind a lovely grip of acidity. Superlength, with great finesse.

instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
  2. Chop all of the fresh vegetables (peppers, onions, celery) into a small dice and mince the garlic.
  3. Over medium-high heat, melt 6 tablespoons butter. Once butter begins to start browning, add the diced vegetables and garlic.
  4. Add about 1 teaspoon salt.
  5. After these have cooked for a few minutes add 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce, 1 teaspoon black pepper, 1 teaspoon nutmeg and 1 teaspoon cayenne pepper. If you like it hot, add a couple shakes of your favorite hot sauce.
  6. Next add about ½ cup of ketchup. Continue cooking and stirring for a few more minutes.
  7. Remove from heat.
  8. After allowing the mixture to cool for a couple of minutes, add about ½ cup of milk. Stir until combined.
  9. Next add at least 1 cup of breadcrumbs. Continue adding breadcrumbs and stirring until mixture is a nice, thick paste.
  10. In a large mixing bowl place the ground beef and pork.
  11. Whisk 3 eggs and add to the meat.
  12. After allowing the pasty vegetable mixture to cool down a bit, begin incorporating it into the meat. Keep working all of the Cajun-Vegetable mix into the meat until all is blended well.
  13. Spray a sheet pan with some non-stick cooking spray.
  14. Next, using your hands, form your meat mixture into a loaf on the sheet pan. Make the loaf around 6-8 inches wide and about 1 ½ inches thick.
  15. In a small bowl or measuring cup, mix together ¾ cup of ketchup with about 2 tablespoons honey. Slather this sauce over the whole meatloaf.
  16. Place in a 400 degree oven for about 40 minutes.
